  RELEVANCE: This article directly addresses power dynamics in defining what counts as philosophy and thus what counts as philosophical literature. For literature review methodology, it exposes how seemingly neutral methodological choices (what sources to include, what languages to prioritize, what standards of argument to apply) can reproduce epistemic hegemony. The proposal for "dialogical exclusive multiplicity" suggests that philosophical literature reviews should not force non-Western traditions into Western frameworks but should recognize multiple autonomous philosophical traditions, each with their own internal standards and development.

