  pages = {19--57},
  doi = {10.1007/978-3-319-99435-2_2},
  note = {
  CORE ARGUMENT: Dougherty analyzes the concept of the scholarly record and how it
  should be corrected when research integrity violations occur. He argues that the
  humanities have fallen short compared to natural sciences in ensuring the
  integrity of the published record. The scholarly record includes not just
  publications but also the web of citations, attributions, and knowledge claims that
